commit.message:
Don't exceed 18002 selectors

* src/encode.c (encode): Don't add more than one dummy selector MTF as
padding. The remaining 6 bits of padding are added by encoding trees
in redundant way. Fixes #18.
(transmit): Make the first code of the first tree coded suboptimally
to add necessary block padding.

Make sure that dummy trees meet Kraft equality

* src/encode.c (generate_prefix_code): Make generated dummy trees meet
Kraft equality so that 7-Zip can decompress lbzip2-compressed
files. Fixes #17.
Silence GCC 7 warnings about implicit fall-through

Avoid using deprecated stdlib functions

* src/divbwt.c (sort_typeBstar): Use memset() instead of bzero().
* src/encode.c (encoder_init, generate_initial_trees, assign_codes,
generate_prefix_code): Likewise.
* src/expand.c (on_input_avail): Likewise.
* src/main.c (xstrtol): Use strchr() instead of index().

Implement running decompressor test cases

* tests/driver.c (test_expand): New function.
(main): Require another command line argument - test mode.  Run test
cases with either test_compress() or test_expand() depending on new
command-line argument.
Create manual-expand test suite from previous test cases
Add fib.bz2 and repet.bz2 to manual-compress test suite
Rename manual compression test suite to manual-compress

Add explicit calls to __gcov_flush()

* configure.ac: Add "-DENABLE_COVERAGE=1" to COVERAGE_CFLAGS. Check
whether __gcov_flush() is defined.
* src/common.h: Define gcov_flush() macro to either __gcov_flush() or
noop, depending on ENABLE_COVERAGE.
* src/main.c (main, version, usage): Call gcov_flush() prior to exiting.
* src/signals.c (bailout, terminate): Likewise.
* src/main.c (main): Terminate program with _exit() instead of
exit().  This reverts commit 2fb7445.
Update copyright date

Add option to enable coverage report generation

* configure.ac: Add --enable-coverage option.
* tests/Makefile.am [ENABLE_COVERAGE]: Generate test coverage report
on check.

Implement new TAP-based test harness

* tests/driver.c: New file.
* tests/manual.test: New file.
* tests/fuzz-collect.test: New file.
* tests/fuzz-divbwt.test: New file.
* tests/Tester: Remove file.
* tests/timeout.c: Remove file.
* tests/Makefile.am: Run new TAP-based test harness.
* configure.ac: Require tap-driver.sh aux file from Automake.

Remove dead branches from transmit()

* src/encode.c (transmit): Add explicit bit buffer dumps where
appropriate.

Convert MERGE_CHECK and GETIDX to functions

* src/divbwt.c (getidx): New function.
(merge_check): Likewise.

Simplify ilog and isqrt functions

* src/divbwt.c (ss_ilg, ss_isqrt, tr_ilg): Expand conditionals to
improve code readability.
Add initial compression test suite

Use exit() instead of _exit() to make gcov work

* src/main.c (main): To terminate the process call exit() instead of
_exit(), otherwise gcov may not work as expected.

Improve lock elision on systems with transactional memory

* src/process.c (up_heap, down_heap): Avoid writing to memory in
common case, when heap contains only one element.
Fix signed-unsigned comparison GCC warnings
Fix GCC 5 _Noreturn warning

Improve memory allocation failure message

* src/main.c (xalloc_die): Improve error message.
Remove unused function prototype

Implement stream mode for parser

* src/parse.c (parser_init): Accept flag for enabling parser stream
mode as additional parameter.

Remove unneeded #include

* src/parse.c: Don't include main.h - Trace() is now declared in
common.h
Fix typos in comments
Add idx899999 test case
Remove -Wmudflap (no longer supported by GCC >= 4.9.0)
Ignore some auto-generated files
Wrap long lines

Implement transmitting into internal buffer

* src/encode.c (transmit): Use an internal buffer if no explicit
external buffer was provided.
* src/encode.h: Update API declaration for transmit();
